  <refsect1>
	<title>Description</title>
	<para>
	  Linked Open Data is a method of publishing machine-readable structured
	  data on the web, using resolveable URIs as the means of
	  identifying the entities described and referred to by the data.
	</para>
	<para>
	  <package>liblod</package> is a library for consuming published
	  Linked Open Data, providing a simple interface for resolving a
	  URI and interrogating the data which is retrieved.
	</para>
  </refsect1>
  
